                <ns0:repositoryURL>http://ozoneaq.gsfc.nasa.gov/omps/</ns0:repositoryURL>
                <ns0:description language="eng">The Ozone Mapping and Profiler Suite measures the ozone layer in our upper
atmosphere&#8212;tracking the status of global ozone distributions, including the
&#8216;ozone hole.&#8217; It also monitors ozone levels in the troposphere, the lowest layer of our
atmosphere. OMPS extends out 40-year long record ozone layer measurements while
also providing improved vertical resolution compared to previous operational
instruments. Closer to the ground, OMPS&#8217;s measurements of harmful ozone
improve air quality monitoring and when combined with cloud predictions; help
to create the Ultraviolet Index, a guide to safe levels of sunlight exposure. OMPS
has two sensors, both new designs, composed of three advanced hyperspectralimaging
spectrometers.The three spectrometers: a downward-looking nadir mapper, nadir profiler and limb profiler. The entire OMPS suite currently fly on board the Suomi NPP spacecraft and are scheduled to fly on the JPSS-2 satellite mission. NASA will provide the OMPS-Limb profiler.</ns0:description>
